Code Formatting:

Follow PEP 8 guidelines for Python code formatting.
Use consistent indentation (4 spaces).
Limit lines to 79 characters where possible.
Error Handling:

Use specific exception handling instead of general exceptions.
Log errors with appropriate severity levels.
Imports:

Remove unused imports.
Use relative imports correctly.
Type Checking:

Use type annotations for function parameters and return types.
Ensure type compatibility in assignments.
Code Organization:

Organize code into logical modules and functions.
Avoid duplicate code.
Logging:

Use logging mechanisms instead of print statements.
Use appropriate logging levels (info, warning, error).
Code Review:

Regularly review code for adherence to these rules.
Use linters and type checkers to identify issues.